BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Motivational Interviewing 2 Day Training
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260728
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260729
DTSTAMP:20260720T121142Z
UID:dartmouth-80960@free-food-dartmouth
DESCRIPTION:Original event page(s):\nhttps://home.dartmouth.edu/events/eve
 nt?event=80960\nhttps://forms.gle/5DKZPUcn6VV3pGmV9\nhttps://mentalhealth.
 dartmouth.edu/strategic-plan/commitment-care\n\nDescription:\nhttps://form
 s.gle/5DKZPUcn6VV3pGmV9\n(Registration)\nSummer 2026 Motivational Intervie
 wing Training—Please register by July 15.\nThe Dialogue Project: Motivat
 ional Interviewing Two-Day Workshop\nTuesday\, July 28 and Thursday\, July
  30\n9 a.m.–4:30 p.m. (morning refreshments available at 8:30 a.m.)\nLoc
 ation: on campus at Dartmouth College\, exact location to be determined\nT
 he Student Wellness Center\, with support from the Dialogue Project\, offe
 rs this intensive\, interactive (and fun!) two-day workshop aimed at build
 ing basic proficiency in Motivational Interviewing (MI). MI is a collabora
 tive communication style for supporting individuals through growth and cha
 nge.\nMI trainings are named in Dartmouth's\nCommitment to Care strategic 
 plan\nas “effective skill-building trainings that support high-quality m
 entoring\, advising\, and teaching.”\nThis evidence-based approach has b
 road application for working with students (and others) and can be an inst
 rumental tool for advisors\, coaches\, facilitators\, and educators. The 
 training is free and open to the entire Dartmouth community. Morning refre
 shments\, snacks\, and lunch will be provided.\nFacilitated by Caitlin Bar
 thelmes\, member of the MI Network of Trainers and LB White of the Student
  Wellness Center.\n*Please attend both days. We offer this training twice 
 a year. If you can't commit to the full training this time\, please plan t
 o attend the event when it is offered in December 2026.\n\nSponsor / organ
 izer: Student Wellness Center\n\nAudience: Public\n\nSource: Dartmouth\n\n
 Why this was included: explicit food-service wording\; food keyword near s
 ervice context\n\nFood availability is inferred from the source listing\; 
 verify details before attending.
LOCATION:To be determined
STATUS:CONFIRMED
URL:https://home.dartmouth.edu/events/event?event=80960
END:VEVENT
